article.headline: TCU 89, St. Gregory's 62
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas -- Edvinas Ruzgas scored a career-high 32 points on Sunday and TCU never trailed in defeating St. Gregory's 89-62. Ruzgas was 7-for-9 from 3-point range and 11-for-13 overall for the Horned Frogs (6-5), who made 52 percent of their shots in the game. TCU built a 27-6 lead about midway through the first half. St. Gregory's got with 30-17 but the Horned Frogs finished the half on a 13-3 run for a 43-20 halftime lead. They led by as many as 35 points in the second half. Zvonko Buljan had 11 points and Garlon Green 10, and Nikola Cerina had eight points and nine rebounds for TCU. Ronnie Moss had a game-high 11 assists. Fayzon Richey scored 20 points for St. Gregory's (5-4), an Oklahoma school that competes in NAIA.
